            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20source%20of%20our%20peace%20is%20our%20right%20standing%20with%20God.%20When%20we%20get%20out%20of%20sorts%20with%20God's%20purpose%20and%20will%2C%20peace%20departs.%20The%20psalmist%2C%20understanding%20this%20relationship%20between%20righteousness%20and%20peace%2C%20declared%2C%20%22Unfailing%20love%20and%20truth%20have%20met%20together.%20Righteousness%20and%20peace%20have%20kissed!%22%20(Psalm%2085%3A10).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul%20prayed%20that%20%22the%20Lord%20of%20peace%20himself%20always%20give%20you%20his%20peace%20no%20matter%20what%20happens%22%20(2%20Thessalonians%203%3A16).%20Our%20actions%20determine%20our%20peace.%20We%20should%20spend%20our%20lives%2C%20therefore%2C%20in%20productive%2C%20focused%20labor.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20Bible%20clearly%20states%20that%20%22whoever%20does%20not%20work%20should%20not%20eat%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(v.%2010).%20To%20be%20%22busy%2C%22%20but%20not%20%22busybodies%2C%22%20means%20that%20we%20know%20our%20jobs%2C%20vocations%2C%20and%20callings%20and%20are%20working%20hard%20every%20day%20to%20accomplish%20them.%20Many%20people%20chase%20idle%20dreams%20and%20foolish%20talk%20but%20never%20produce%20anything.%20Consequently%2C%20they%20grow%20frustrated%20and%20lose%20their%20peace.%20If%20we%20will%20work%20hard%20and%20%22never%20get%20tired%20of%20doing%20good%22%20(2%20Thessalonians%203%3A13)%2C%20however%2C%20then%20the%20Lord%20of%20peace%20will%20give%20us%20peace.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHave%20you%20lost%20your%20peace%3F%20Find%20your%20work%2C%20and%20you%20will%20find%20your%20peace.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Jeremiah.26:1-27:22",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EJeremiah%2026%3A1-27%3A22%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_1%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJeremiah%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJeremiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Escape%20from%20Death%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20message%20came%20to%20Jeremiah%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20early%20in%20the%20reign%20of%20Jehoiakim%20son%20of%20Josiah%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20first%20year%20of%20Jehoiakim%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20was%20608%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20king%20of%20Judah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_2%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20Stand%20in%20the%20courtyard%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20and%20make%20an%20announcement%20to%20the%20people%20who%20have%20come%20there%20to%20worship%20from%20all%20over%20Judah.%20Give%20them%20my%20entire%20message%3B%20include%20every%20word.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_3%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EPerhaps%20they%20will%20listen%20and%20turn%20from%20their%20evil%20ways.%20Then%20I%20will%20change%20my%20mind%20about%20the%20disaster%20I%20am%20ready%20to%20pour%20out%20on%20them%20because%20of%20their%20sins.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_4%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BSay%20to%20them%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20If%20you%20will%20not%20listen%20to%20me%20and%20obey%20my%20word%20I%20have%20given%20you%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_5%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20if%20you%20will%20not%20listen%20to%20my%20servants%2C%20the%20prophets%26%23x2014%3Bfor%20I%20sent%20them%20again%20and%20again%20to%20warn%20you%2C%20but%20you%20would%20not%20listen%20to%20them%26%23x2014%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_6%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3Ethen%20I%20will%20destroy%20this%20Temple%20as%20I%20destroyed%20Shiloh%2C%20the%20place%20where%20the%20Tabernacle%20was%20located.%20And%20I%20will%20make%20Jerusalem%20an%20object%20of%20cursing%20in%20every%20nation%20on%20earth.%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_7%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20priests%2C%20the%20prophets%2C%20and%20all%20the%20people%20listened%20to%20Jeremiah%20as%20he%20spoke%20in%20front%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_8%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20when%20Jeremiah%20had%20finished%20his%20message%2C%20saying%20everything%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20told%20him%20to%20say%2C%20the%20priests%20and%20prophets%20and%20all%20the%20people%20at%20the%20Temple%20mobbed%20him.%20%26%23x201C%3BKill%20him!%26%23x201D%3B%20they%20shouted.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_9%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20right%20do%20you%20have%20to%20prophesy%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20name%20that%20this%20Temple%20will%20be%20destroyed%20like%20Shiloh%3F%20What%20do%20you%20mean%2C%20saying%20that%20Jerusalem%20will%20be%20destroyed%20and%20left%20with%20no%20inhabitants%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20And%20all%20the%20people%20threatened%20him%20as%20he%20stood%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Temple.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_10%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20the%20officials%20of%20Judah%20heard%20what%20was%20happening%2C%20they%20rushed%20over%20from%20the%20palace%20and%20sat%20down%20at%20the%20New%20Gate%20of%20the%20Temple%20to%20hold%20court.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_11%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20priests%20and%20prophets%20presented%20their%20accusations%20to%20the%20officials%20and%20the%20people.%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20man%20should%20die!%26%23x201D%3B%20they%20said.%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20have%20heard%20with%20your%20own%20ears%20what%20a%20traitor%20he%20is%2C%20for%20he%20has%20prophesied%20against%20this%20city.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_12%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jeremiah%20spoke%20to%20the%20officials%20and%20the%20people%20in%20his%20own%20defense.%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20sent%20me%20to%20prophesy%20against%20this%20Temple%20and%20this%20city%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20said.%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20gave%20me%20every%20word%20that%20I%20have%20spoken.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_13%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20if%20you%20stop%20your%20sinning%20and%20begin%20to%20obey%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%2C%20he%20will%20change%20his%20mind%20about%20this%20disaster%20that%20he%20has%20announced%20against%20you.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_14%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20for%20me%2C%20I%20am%20in%20your%20hands%26%23x2014%3Bdo%20with%20me%20as%20you%20think%20best.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_15%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20if%20you%20kill%20me%2C%20rest%20assured%20that%20you%20will%20be%20killing%20an%20innocent%20man!%20The%20responsibility%20for%20such%20a%20deed%20will%20lie%20on%20you%2C%20on%20this%20city%2C%20and%20on%20every%20person%20living%20in%20it.%20For%20it%20is%20absolutely%20true%20that%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20sent%20me%20to%20speak%20every%20word%20you%20have%20heard.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_16%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20officials%20and%20the%20people%20said%20to%20the%20priests%20and%20prophets%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20man%20does%20not%20deserve%20the%20death%20sentence%2C%20for%20he%20has%20spoken%20to%20us%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20our%20God.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_17%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20some%20of%20the%20wise%20old%20men%20stood%20and%20spoke%20to%20all%20the%20people%20assembled%20there.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_18%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BRemember%20when%20Micah%20of%20Moresheth%20prophesied%20during%20the%20reign%20of%20King%20Hezekiah%20of%20Judah.%20He%20told%20the%20people%20of%20Judah%2C%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-sp%22%3E%26%23x2018%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20Heaven%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Armies%20says%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EMount%20Zion%20will%20be%20plowed%20like%20an%20open%20field%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3EJerusalem%20will%20be%20reduced%20to%20ruins!%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1%22%3EA%20thicket%20will%20grow%20on%20the%20heights%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Ewhere%20the%20Temple%20now%20stands.%26%23x2019%3B%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E26%3A18%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Mic%203%3A12.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_19%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20did%20King%20Hezekiah%20and%20the%20people%20kill%20him%20for%20saying%20this%3F%20No%2C%20they%20turned%20from%20their%20sins%20and%20worshiped%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20They%20begged%20him%20for%20mercy.%20Then%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20changed%20his%20mind%20about%20the%20terrible%20disaster%20he%20had%20pronounced%20against%20them.%20So%20we%20are%20about%20to%20do%20ourselves%20great%20harm.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_20%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20this%20time%20Uriah%20son%20of%20Shemaiah%20from%20Kiriath-jearim%20was%20also%20prophesying%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20And%20he%20predicted%20the%20same%20terrible%20disaster%20against%20the%20city%20and%20nation%20as%20Jeremiah%20did.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_21%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20King%20Jehoiakim%20and%20the%20army%20officers%20and%20officials%20heard%20what%20he%20was%20saying%2C%20the%20king%20sent%20someone%20to%20kill%20him.%20But%20Uriah%20heard%20about%20the%20plan%20and%20escaped%20in%20fear%20to%20Egypt.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_22%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20King%20Jehoiakim%20sent%20Elnathan%20son%20of%20Acbor%20to%20Egypt%20along%20with%20several%20other%20men%20to%20capture%20Uriah.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_23%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20took%20him%20prisoner%20and%20brought%20him%20back%20to%20King%20Jehoiakim.%20The%20king%20then%20killed%20Uriah%20with%20a%20sword%20and%20had%20him%20buried%20in%20an%20unmarked%20grave.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_26_24%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3ENevertheless%2C%20Ahikam%20son%20of%20Shaphan%20stood%20up%20for%20Jeremiah%20and%20persuaded%20the%20court%20not%20to%20turn%20him%20over%20to%20the%20mob%20to%20be%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_1%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EJeremiah%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJeremiah%20Wears%20an%20Ox%20Yoke%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20message%20came%20to%20Jeremiah%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20early%20in%20the%20reign%20of%20Zedekiah%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E27%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20some%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%20and%20Syriac%20version%20(see%20also%2027%3A3%2C%2012)%3B%20most%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%20read%20%3Cem%3EJehoiakim.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20son%20of%20Josiah%2C%20king%20of%20Judah.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_2%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20said%20to%20me%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BMake%20a%20yoke%2C%20and%20fasten%20it%20on%20your%20neck%20with%20leather%20straps.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_3%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20send%20messages%20to%20the%20kings%20of%20Edom%2C%20Moab%2C%20Ammon%2C%20Tyre%2C%20and%20Sidon%20through%20their%20ambassadors%20who%20have%20come%20to%20see%20King%20Zedekiah%20in%20Jerusalem.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_4%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EGive%20them%20this%20message%20for%20their%20masters%3A%20%26%23x2018%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20Heaven%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Armies%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20says%3A%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_5%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EWith%20my%20great%20strength%20and%20powerful%20arm%20I%20made%20the%20earth%20and%20all%20its%20people%20and%20every%20animal.%20I%20can%20give%20these%20things%20of%20mine%20to%20anyone%20I%20choose.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_6%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20I%20will%20give%20your%20countries%20to%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar%20of%20Babylon%2C%20who%20is%20my%20servant.%20I%20have%20put%20everything%2C%20even%20the%20wild%20animals%2C%20under%20his%20control.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_7%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EAll%20the%20nations%20will%20serve%20him%2C%20his%20son%2C%20and%20his%20grandson%20until%20his%20time%20is%20up.%20Then%20many%20nations%20and%20great%20kings%20will%20conquer%20and%20rule%20over%20Babylon.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_8%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20you%20must%20submit%20to%20Babylon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20king%20and%20serve%20him%3B%20put%20your%20neck%20under%20Babylon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20yoke!%20I%20will%20punish%20any%20nation%20that%20refuses%20to%20be%20his%20slave%2C%20says%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20I%20will%20send%20war%2C%20famine%2C%20and%20disease%20upon%20that%20nation%20until%20Babylon%20has%20conquered%20it.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_9%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3B%26%23x2018%3BDo%20not%20listen%20to%20your%20false%20prophets%2C%20fortune-tellers%2C%20interpreters%20of%20dreams%2C%20mediums%2C%20and%20sorcerers%20who%20say%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20king%20of%20Babylon%20will%20not%20conquer%20you.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_10%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20are%20all%20liars%2C%20and%20their%20lies%20will%20lead%20to%20your%20being%20driven%20out%20of%20your%20land.%20I%20will%20drive%20you%20out%20and%20send%20you%20far%20away%20to%20die.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_11%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20people%20of%20any%20nation%20that%20submits%20to%20the%20king%20of%20Babylon%20will%20be%20allowed%20to%20stay%20in%20their%20own%20country%20to%20farm%20the%20land%20as%20usual.%20I%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20have%20spoken!%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_12%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20I%20repeated%20this%20same%20message%20to%20King%20Zedekiah%20of%20Judah.%20%26%23x201C%3BIf%20you%20want%20to%20live%2C%20submit%20to%20the%20yoke%20of%20the%20king%20of%20Babylon%20and%20his%20people.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22jere_27_13%22%20bk%3D%22jere%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EWhy%20do%20you%20insist%20on%20dying%26%23x2014%3Byou%20and%20your%20people%3F%20Why%20should%20you%20choose%20war%2C%20famine%2C%20and%20disease%2C%20which%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20will%20bring%20against%20every%20nation%20that%20refuses%20to%20submit%20to%20Babylon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20king%3F%20%3C%2Fverse_exp